[This has been a prominent year for _Yersinia pestis_ infections in the USA, with 8 reported cases including 3 fatalities, and with one of the cases presenting in Georgia (the 1st case reported in that state) but acquired in California. The manifestations of _Yersinia pestis_ infection in this case are not stated, although overall 95 percent of cases are bubonic in nature. Deaths from plague generally occur from septicemic or pneumonic plague. Only pneumonic plague can be spread from person to person.

The HealthMap/ProMED map of Bernalillo County, New Mexico, United States can be found at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3595447,1843 - Mod.LL]
